This repository contains the Kaltura Avatar SDK for embedding AI-powered video avatar conversations in websites.

## Two SDKs (not versions — different integration approaches)

### Socket SDK (`sdk-socket/`) — Full control
- Direct Socket.IO + WebRTC connection
- You own the <video> element
- Built-in GenUI rendering (charts, tables, code, diagrams)
- Real-time events, auto-reconnect, extensible plugins
- Source: `sdk-socket/src/kaltura-avatar-sdk.js`
- CDN: `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/kaltura/conversational-avatar-embed-sdk@latest/sdk-socket/dist/kaltura-avatar-sdk.js`
- Peer dep: Socket.IO client v4

### Iframe SDK (`sdk-iframe/`) — Drop-in simple
- Sandboxed iframe + postMessage
- Zero dependencies, ~6KB minified
- Automatic UI handling
- Source: `sdk-iframe/kaltura-avatar-sdk.min.js`
- CDN: `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/kaltura/conversational-avatar-embed-sdk@latest/sdk-iframe/kaltura-avatar-sdk.min.js`

## Key Patterns

### Socket SDK
```javascript
const sdk = new KalturaAvatarSDK({ clientId: '...', flowId: '...', container: '#avatar' });
sdk.on('avatar-speech', ({ text }) => console.log(text));
sdk.on('user-speech', ({ text, isFinal }) => { if (isFinal) console.log(text); });
sdk.on('genui', ({ type, data }) => { /* charts, tables, code, etc. */ });
sdk.connect();

// Send text instead of speaking
sdk.sendText('Hello');

// Inject runtime context
sdk.injectDPP({ user: { name: 'Jane' }, inst: ['Be concise.'] });

// Register spoken command triggers
sdk.registerCommand('end', 'ending call now', () => sdk.disconnect());
```

### Iframe SDK
```javascript
const sdk = new KalturaAvatarSDK({ clientId: '...', flowId: '...', container: '#avatar' });

sdk.on('showing-agent', () => {
  setTimeout(() => sdk.injectPrompt(JSON.stringify({ greeting: "Hello!" })), 500);
});

sdk.on('agent-talked', (data) => {
  const text = (data?.agentContent || data || '').toLowerCase();
  if (text.includes('ending call now')) { sdk.end(); }
});

await sdk.start();
```

## When building apps with this SDK
1. Default to Socket SDK unless user needs iframe isolation
2. Always inject DPP on ready/showing-agent events
3. Use spoken commands to trigger JS actions (avatar says trigger phrase → your code runs)
4. Both SDKs connect to same Kaltura backend — same avatars, same Knowledge Base

## Testing
```bash
cd sdk-socket && npm test  # 125 unit + GenUI tests
```
